// Access modifiers//

help access control thr access to the class properties/attributes and methods

private   // can be access inly within the class
default    //can be access anywhere withnin the package
protected  //can be access inside the chils class
public     // access form anyehere in program

method declaration:
0.1. access modifier //optioanl
1.return type()  //mandtory
2.name;   //mandtory
3.()  //mandetory
4. {} //mandetory
==============
Rule:
always try to declare a properties as PRIVATE
and difime the methods to change that pro[erties - gives us
more control over that properties;
